                            <img aria-hidden="true" src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/415s-zIcqHL.jpg" class="resource-thumbnail" />
                            <div class="resource-content">
                                <h4><i data-feather="book"></i><u>Bias</u> by Jennifer Eberhardt</h4>
                                <p>
                                    With a perspective that is simultaneously scientific, investigative, and informed by personal experience, Dr. Jennifer Eberhardt, social psychologist of Stanford, provides an exceptional examination of the effects, causes, and possible mitigation of bias. From prisons to her own life she examines how bias causes the racism we see in the world and then offers us tools to address it. While bias’s grasp seems almost inescapable, Eberhardt shows through experimentation and brilliant scientific explanation how we can overcome it. The ideas presented provide an approach applicable to much more than just police misconduct.
                                </p>
                                <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Biased-Uncovering-Hidden-Prejudice-Shapes-ebook/dp/B07DH89ZDY" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                   type="button" class="btn btn-outline-info">
                                    Amazon
