                            <div class="resource-content">
                                <h4><i data-feather="book"></i><u>Between the World and Me</u> by Ta-Nehisi Coates</h4>
                                <p>
                                    Ta-Nehisi Coates’ Between the World and Me, a letter to his 15-year-old son, is an intimate insight into Coates’s life and thoughts as a black man and now a black father. Coates wants so much for his son but worries that it will all be taken away as America has done to black people in the past. While not as academic as the other books listed, Between the World and Me still manages to masterfully teach and provoke thought in a personal and exploratory narrative.
                                </p>
                                <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Between-World-Me-Ta-Nehisi-Coates/dp/0451482212" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                   type="button" class="btn btn-outline-info">
                                    Amazon
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="resource">
                            <img aria-hidden="true" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/B0pc4ZmCcAAGOa2.png:large" class="resource-thumbnail" />
                            <div class="resource-content">
                                <h4><a href="https://www.themarshallproject.org/"><i data-feather="globe"></i>The Marshall Project</a></h4>
                                <p>
                                    The Marshall Project is a nonpartisan, nonprofit news organization that seeks to create and sustain a sense of national urgency about the U.S. criminal justice system. They achieve this through award-winning journalism, partnerships with other news outlets and public forums. In all of our work they strive to educate and enlarge the audience of people who care about the state of criminal justice.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="resource">
