                                <h4><i data-feather="music"></i>I Can't Breathe - H.E.R</h4>
                                <p>
                                    <i>I Can't Breathe</i> by H.E.R. won 2021 Song of the Year at the Grammys. She wrote it in response to the recent spate of police killings of unarmed black citizens and the swell of protests against police brutality and systemic racism during the BLM Protests. In a somber blue style with acoustic notes, H.E.R. sings what black America feels.
                                </p>
